      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI TO SUCCESS (7) resumed with an encouraging fourth Leap To Fame in the Kilmore Cup before a terrific effort in the Hunter Cup, working home well to be beaten only 3m. Draws wide his form reads strongly for this and he strikes at 50 per cent when third-up so should be at his peak. SMOKEN ACE NZ (5) is in a purple patch of form having made it three wins on the trot by setting a new track record with his last-start Listed win at Kilmore. Has had four weeks off since but has been kept up to the mark with a nice trial. MACH DAN (6) has placed in four of his last five starts. Was 4m behind Smoken Ace two back before leading from one spot wider than this and sticking on here last time. Can give a sight again. GHOST OF TIME (2) is up in grade but draws well and added to a string of wins and placings by scoring at this circuit and distance last time so respect.",
